Authorities are on high alert following an outbreak of the disease was confirmed in Zimbabwe. JOHANNESBURG The National Institute for Communicable Diseases says it has plans in place to prevent typhoid fever from reaching South Africa.An outbreak of the disease has been confirmed in Zimbabwe.The institute s Lucille Blumberg says health authorities are on high alert. We ve a lot of travelers from South Africa who enjoy December holidays in Zimbabwe and clearly they may be at risk for contracted typhoid. I think it s important to alert returning travelers and also our health facilities to be aware of typhoid. 